'doc' Spatz,<br><br>
When someone gives a name privately and requests it not be used publically, I honor that request.  I assume that Doc Del gave you the same information he gave me.  Please realize that opening one's family to the kinds of attacks he has received (not from you) can be very unsettling.<br><br>
Concerning the Vietnamese Americans and their contribution to our society, just wait, 'cause you ain't seen nothin' yet.  The Liens of this country are just about to graduate, and some already have (I believe about 3 years ago the US Air Force Academy had its first Vietnamese/American graduate).<br><br>
Would you deny a whole population the right to participate in our democracy because of the language barrier?  Citizenship doesn't require complete fluency in English, and some concepts are difficult to grasp without years of speaking/learning in English.<br><br>
